sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1819006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Constitutive promotor from Anderson library (BBa_J23106) assembled to green fluorescent protein attached to linker (BBa_S05308). This part was used to characterize BBa_K1819000 and compare its efficiency to green fluorescent protein derived from jellyfish Aequeora victoria wild-type GFP (BBa_E0040).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: La??s Ribovski
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part results from the assembly of BBa_J23106 and BBa_S05308

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: NdeI+E0040
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: GFP coding sequence with an N-terminal linker
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Designed by Brasil-USP team, BBa_K1819000 is a GFP coding sequence with an N-terminal linker, which is 5???-flanked by NdeI restriction site. It allows to characterize protein expression and secretion, and may serve to other IGEM teams that would like to express a chimera C-terminally attached to GFP, which exhibits bright green fluorescence when exposed to light in the blue to ultraviolet range. Such non-usual restriction site, NdeI restriction site, was placed for cloning purposes that lead to expression of recombinant protein with no additional amino acid residue(s) between its coding sequence and the fused N-terminal tag.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lais Ribovski
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: GFP coding sequence source is BBa_E0040 (http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_E0040)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: As a design consideration we highlight that we chose to add the NdeI restriction site to a GFP coding sequence to avoid any additional amino acid residue between coding sequence and the fused N-terminal tag.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
